snippet.textDisplay:
There are some guys saying this one is better than the original.
Sorry guys but I will be "that" guy who shoots you down. The body of work that Nusrat Sahib produced is flawless and near perfect. No matter how many times the Mona Lisa is copied. It'll always be Da Vinci who did it best. Same goes with the masterpeices created by Ustad Nusrat. "Often imitated but never duplicated".
Also this song misses so many poetic verses from the original that I fail to feel it on the same level. 
If treated as a seperate body of work entirely from the original then this song is good. So I encourage people not to compare this one with Ustad Nusrat's. Treat it as a seperate entity because no one will ever come close to the Shehanshah e Qawwali. Not even Rahat. So stop drawing comparisons. Enjoy this one and be mesmerised by the original one.
